### ğŸ“ Dataset

* **Name:** Mall Customer Segmentation Data
* **Source:** [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/vjchoudhary7/customer-segmentation-tutorial-in-python)
* **Columns Typically Included:**

  * `CustomerID`
  * `Gender`
  * `Age`
  * `Annual Income (k$)`
  * `Spending Score (1-100)`

---
You can find it at https://github.com/elevvo-machine-learning/Task1/blob/main/README.md 


And test it via this link : https://student-score-ikedid.streamlit.app/
### ğŸ’» How to Run

1. Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

2. Run the app:

```bash
streamlit run customer_segmentation_app.py
```

3. Upload your dataset and interactively explore the customer segments.

---

### ğŸ§ª Example Use Case

A marketing analyst or retail manager can use this tool to:

* Group customers into segments for targeted campaigns
* Identify high-value vs. low-engagement customers
* Understand income vs. spending behavior patterns

